31 SUMMARY
3322 PART A
33 This Part makes appropriations and allocations of funds for fiscal years 2025-26 and
34 2026-27.
35 PART B
36 This Part provides that the funding for the Local Road Assistance Program is calculated
37 based on the Highway Fund allocation for the general construction and maintenance of
38 highways and bridges.
39 PART C
Page 45 - 132LR2411(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to H.P. 178, L.D. 274
1 This Part sets the attrition rate for the 2026-2027 biennium from 1.6% to 5% for
2 executive branch departments and agencies.
3 PART D
4 This Part requires the State Controller to transfer amounts exceeding $100,000 from
5 the unallocated balance in the Highway Fund after all commitments to the Highway and
6 Bridge Capital, Highway Light Capital, Maintenance and Operations and multimodal
7 transportation programs within the Department of Transportation for capital needs.
8 PART E
9 This Part authorizes the Commissioner of Transportation to transfer Highway Fund
10 Personal Services balances available at the end of fiscal years 2025-26 and 2026-27 to the
11 Department of Transportation Highway and Bridge Capital, Highway Light Capital,
12 Maintenance and Operations and multimodal transportation programs for capital or all
13 other needs. The funds may be allocated by financial order upon the recommendation of
14 the State Budget Officer and the approval of the Governor.
1155 PART F
16 Part F amends the authority granted by Public Law 2023, chapter 189 to issue a
17 TransCap revenue bond from the TransCap Trust Fund at the Maine Municipal Bond Bank.
18 It increases the size of the bond authorized from $200,000,000 to $250,000,000 and allows
19 a longer time in which to issue the bonds. These bond proceeds are used for capital
20 transportation infrastructure projects.
21 This Part also simplifies, increases and diversifies the revenue streams transferred to
22 the TransCap Trust Fund for revenue bond debt service and underwriting requirements.
23 This Part continues the existing portion of fuel taxes and adds a portion of the sales tax
24 related to automobiles transferred to the Highway Fund as revenue streams so that bond
25 proceeds can be used for all highway, bridge and multimodal transportation capital
26 projects. This Part also eliminates the transfer of the portion of registration fees that went
27 to the TransCap Trust Fund.
28 PART G
29 This Part provides that the unexpended Highway Fund account balances for
30 purchasing, operating, maintaining, improving, repairing, constructing and managing the
31 assets of multimodal forms of transportation do not lapse.
